WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.990 --> 00:00:10.931
<v Mike Demopoulos> Hello, and welcome to the next session

2
00:00:10.931 --> 00:00:13.946
of the WordPress Accessibility Day. 

3
00:00:13.946 --> 00:00:16.192
I am your host, Mike Demo, 

4
00:00:16.192 --> 00:00:19.352
and helping us in the chat moderator, 

5
00:00:19.352 --> 00:00:21.099
is Kayla Demopoulos. 

6
00:00:21.099 --> 00:00:24.726
Our next session is 
going to be by Joe Hall. 

7
00:00:24.726 --> 00:00:27.397
Joe has been a WordPress developer 

8
00:00:27.397 --> 00:00:29.763
and SEO for the last 11 years. 

9
00:00:29.763 --> 00:00:31.609
He first became interested 

10
00:00:31.609 --> 00:00:34.685
in Accessibility Consulting 
back in the 90s, 

11
00:00:34.685 --> 00:00:36.546
but mostly does technical SEO 

12
00:00:36.546 --> 00:00:38.221
for medium-sized companies,

13
00:00:38.221 --> 00:00:40.826
non-profit, and enterprise level brands.

14
00:00:40.826 --> 00:00:43.204
He is passionate 
about accessible, 

15
00:00:43.204 --> 00:00:47.907
highly optimized, 
and fast WordPress themes. 

16
00:00:47.907 --> 00:00:50.906
Joe's talk is 
going to be about 

17
00:00:50.906 --> 00:00:54.404
SEO and Web Accessibility: 
Partners for a Better Internet. 

18
00:00:54.404 --> 00:00:59.155
If you have any questions, 
please make sure to put them into the chat,

19
00:00:59.155 --> 00:01:01.431
and we will get those at the end. 

20
00:01:01.431 --> 00:01:05.437
Please remember that there is 
a code of conduct for this event, 

21
00:01:05.437 --> 00:01:08.200
and we're all part of 
the same WordPress community. 

22
00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:17.780
With that, thank you so much, 
and welcome, Joe!

23
00:01:24.780 --> 00:01:28.001
<v Joe Hall> I am looking forward 
to this conversation!

24
00:01:28.001 --> 00:01:32.020
I'm gonna start my slides, here.

25
00:01:32.020 --> 00:01:41.259
This talk is called SEO and Web Accessibility:
Partners for a Better Internet.

26
00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:44.677
I'm going to get started here. 

27
00:01:44.677 --> 00:01:50.079
Let's get started 
with some definitions.

28
00:01:50.079 --> 00:01:56.837
This talk is geared towards folks 
that are interested in SEO, 

29
00:01:56.837 --> 00:02:02.118
but also for folks that are 
interested in accessibility, obviously.

30
00:02:02.118 --> 00:02:06.668
Because we're talking 
to two separate groups, 

31
00:02:06.668 --> 00:02:12.692
I thought it might be smart 
to do some basic definitions, 

32
00:02:12.692 --> 00:02:16.077
so that we're all 
on the same page. 

33
00:02:16.077 --> 00:02:20.301
When we talk about 
web accessibility, 

34
00:02:20.301 --> 00:02:24.061
web accessibility is 
the inclusive practice 

35
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:27.309
of ensuring there is 
no barriers that 

36
00:02:27.309 --> 00:02:30.722
prevent interaction with or access 

37
00:02:30.722 --> 00:02:34.135
to websites on the world wide web,

38
00:02:34.135 --> 00:02:38.230
for people with 
all types of disabilities.

39
00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:40.080
When we talk about SEO, 

40
00:02:40.080 --> 00:02:43.969
we're talking about 
search engine optimization, 

41
00:02:43.969 --> 00:02:50.195
the process of increasing the quality 
and quantity of website traffic, 

42
00:02:50.195 --> 00:02:55.367
by increasing the visibility 
of a website or web page

43
00:02:55.367 --> 00:02:58.685
to users of a web search engine. 

44
00:02:58.685 --> 00:03:04.548
This may involve increasing rankings 
found within the results, 

45
00:03:04.548 --> 00:03:07.655
or improving the presentation

46
00:03:07.655 --> 00:03:11.190
of existing listings or rankings.

47
00:03:11.190 --> 00:03:15.810
And one of the really
interesting aspects 

48
00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:18.937
of SEO and web accessibility 
as a practice, 

49
00:03:18.937 --> 00:03:22.064
if this is something 
you do professionally, 

50
00:03:22.064 --> 00:03:25.363
or you're just interested in it, 

51
00:03:25.363 --> 00:03:28.462
these two things can influence 

52
00:03:28.462 --> 00:03:33.060
many of the same areas 
of product development.

53
00:03:33.060 --> 00:03:36.343
They both touch on user experience, 

54
00:03:36.343 --> 00:03:39.716
design and information architecture, 

55
00:03:39.716 --> 00:03:41.540
content development,

56
00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:45.964
and content optimization 
and technical infrastructure. 

57
00:03:45.964 --> 00:03:47.452
So it makes sense 

58
00:03:47.452 --> 00:03:51.091
that if there are 
so many overlapping areas 

59
00:03:51.091 --> 00:03:52.674
that we should be working

60
00:03:52.674 --> 00:03:56.189
closer together to each other.

61
00:03:56.189 --> 00:03:59.351
It might be smart 
to dispel some myths,

62
00:03:59.351 --> 00:04:01.880
because there are lots of myths 

63
00:04:01.880 --> 00:04:03.852
around both practices 

64
00:04:03.852 --> 00:04:07.529
and it's smart to be 
on the same page. 

65
00:04:07.529 --> 00:04:09.320
So myth number one:

66
00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:11.222
Accessibility is only focused 

67
00:04:11.222 --> 00:04:14.203
on improving access 
for the visually impaired. 

68
00:04:14.203 --> 00:04:17.983
I see a lot of SEOs 
with this myth

69
00:04:17.983 --> 00:04:22.319
and the truth 
is that accessibility

70
00:04:22.319 --> 00:04:25.997
is focused on lots of 
different types of disabilities:

71
00:04:25.997 --> 00:04:27.334
visual impairments, 

72
00:04:27.334 --> 00:04:29.340
motor or mobility impairments,

73
00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:32.391
auditory or hearing impairments, 

74
00:04:32.391 --> 00:04:34.238
seizure disorders, 

75
00:04:34.238 --> 00:04:38.030
cognitive or 
intellectual disabilities.

76
00:04:38.030 --> 00:04:43.059
We're talking about 
a cross disability spectrum, 

77
00:04:43.059 --> 00:04:46.035
not just visual impairments. 

78
00:04:46.035 --> 00:04:52.484
Myth number two: SEO is only about 
optimizing content with keywords. 

79
00:04:52.484 --> 00:04:54.224
This comes up a lot 

80
00:04:54.224 --> 00:04:59.530
with folks that have 
a cursory understanding of SEO.

81
00:04:59.530 --> 00:05:04.897
The truth is that SEO follows 
technical best practices. 

82
00:05:04.897 --> 00:05:10.088
It looks at external signals, 
such as links or citations. 

83
00:05:10.088 --> 00:05:15.189
It informs the design or 
information architecture process

84
00:05:15.189 --> 00:05:20.260
and then, of course, it does focus 
on content optimization. 

85
00:05:20.260 --> 00:05:25.185
Another myth that I hear 
a lot of SEOs make is that

86
00:05:25.185 --> 00:05:30.389
excellent SEO means 
full accessibility or vice versa,

87
00:05:30.389 --> 00:05:33.941
and that full accessibility 
means excellent SEO. 

88
00:05:33.941 --> 00:05:36.478
And we'll take a look 
in this talk 

89
00:05:36.478 --> 00:05:41.043
about how the two practices 
overlap each other

90
00:05:41.043 --> 00:05:45.219
and how having good accessibility, 
can mean

91
00:05:45.219 --> 00:05:46.878
in some ways, that you do, 

92
00:05:46.878 --> 00:05:49.520
when you're doing 
the right thing for SEO, 

93
00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:53.360
and then vice versa 
with SEO for accessibility, 

94
00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:55.972
but it's a myth to assume 

95
00:05:55.972 --> 00:05:59.161
that just because 
you have great accessibility 

96
00:05:59.161 --> 00:06:02.824
that somehow you're 
going to do really well with SEO. 

97
00:06:02.824 --> 00:06:05.429
Or that just because 
you have great SEO, 

98
00:06:05.429 --> 00:06:08.264
that you know your website 
is accessible. 

99
00:06:08.264 --> 00:06:10.228
That's just not the case 

100
00:06:10.228 --> 00:06:13.919
and we'll look into
that in a moment.

101
00:06:13.919 --> 00:06:15.785
Let's start talking about 

102
00:06:15.785 --> 00:06:18.870
some of the areas of 
overlap and conflict. 

103
00:06:18.870 --> 00:06:22.038
I've put together 
a Venn diagram here 

104
00:06:22.038 --> 00:06:25.705
and everything that's 
listed on this diagram

105
00:06:25.705 --> 00:06:29.150
is of course not a complete list 
of either practice. 

106
00:06:29.150 --> 00:06:32.140
This is just an example of 
some of the things 

107
00:06:32.140 --> 00:06:34.948
that might be found 
in each area 

108
00:06:34.948 --> 00:06:37.416
and how some things overlap. 

109
00:06:37.416 --> 00:06:40.560
On the left side, 
I have SEO 

110
00:06:40.560 --> 00:06:45.488
and in the SEO quadrant 
of this Venn diagram 

111
00:06:45.488 --> 00:06:50.136
I have listed page speed, 
structured data, 

112
00:06:50.136 --> 00:06:54.539
external links, mobile indexing, 
and AMP? 

113
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:58.507
On the accessibility-only section 

114
00:06:58.507 --> 00:07:01.658
of the Venn diagram I have 

115
00:07:01.658 --> 00:07:04.225
ARIA, screen readers,

116
00:07:04.225 --> 00:07:08.358
HTML landmarks, keyboard access, 

117
00:07:08.358 --> 00:07:10.378
and form optimization. 

118
00:07:10.378 --> 00:07:13.531
Some of the main, 
shared areas, 

119
00:07:13.531 --> 00:07:18.138
that overlap between SEO 
and accessibility are

120
00:07:18.138 --> 00:07:20.872
information architecture. 

121
00:07:20.872 --> 00:07:23.453
We use some anchor text, 

122
00:07:23.453 --> 00:07:25.621
content optimization 

123
00:07:25.621 --> 00:07:27.629
and media optimization. 

124
00:07:27.629 --> 00:07:29.578
We'll take a look at 

125
00:07:29.578 --> 00:07:32.919
some of these 
overlapping areas now 

126
00:07:32.919 --> 00:07:35.206
and see how they work together 

127
00:07:35.206 --> 00:07:38.969
and how sometimes they
can cause conflicts as well.

128
00:07:38.969 --> 00:07:44.385
We'll start off with 
information architecture.

129
00:07:44.385 --> 00:07:47.554
With navigation items for SEO, 

130
00:07:47.554 --> 00:07:53.790
navigation items should follow 
the information architecture, 

131
00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:56.675
have simple but descriptive labels 

132
00:07:56.675 --> 00:07:59.972
and point to main sections 
of the site.

133
00:07:59.972 --> 00:08:01.940
For SEO, this is great, 

134
00:08:01.940 --> 00:08:06.121
because these help build 
internal links site-wide,

135
00:08:06.121 --> 00:08:08.663
which helps spread link equity 

136
00:08:08.663 --> 00:08:11.101
and helps the search engines 

137
00:08:11.101 --> 00:08:14.464
find all the main sections of the site. 

138
00:08:14.464 --> 00:08:17.662
For accessibility, 
navigation items 

139
00:08:17.662 --> 00:08:22.195
should have a simple 
and descriptive labels 

140
00:08:22.195 --> 00:08:26.776
and this is primarily 
for ease of navigation 

141
00:08:26.776 --> 00:08:31.429
and those navigation items 
should be easy 

142
00:08:31.429 --> 00:08:36.730
for the user to understand 
and find easily. 

143
00:08:39.298 --> 00:08:41.000
Unordered list. 

144
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.581
In HTML, we have 
different types of lists. 

145
00:08:45.581 --> 00:08:47.371
We have unordered list 
and numbered list. 

146
00:08:48.371 --> 00:08:49.663
Typically when we're making 

147
00:08:49.663 --> 00:08:53.251
an information architecture 
or navigation, 

148
00:08:53.251 --> 00:08:56.840
we'll use an unordered list 
and then also, 

149
00:08:56.840 --> 00:09:01.463
we'll use it for things
like tertiary navigation 

150
00:09:01.463 --> 00:09:03.350
as well on the page.

151
00:09:03.350 --> 00:09:07.251
Search engines prefer 
organized content

152
00:09:07.251 --> 00:09:10.471
and clean HTML for navigation. 

153
00:09:10.471 --> 00:09:14.163
An unordered list is really great 
for search engines, 

154
00:09:14.163 --> 00:09:16.556
because they can easily understand 

155
00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:21.406
that these links 
belong together as a set 

156
00:09:21.406 --> 00:09:25.376
and they'll either parse those 

157
00:09:25.376 --> 00:09:29.100
as parts of the featured snippet, 

158
00:09:29.100 --> 00:09:32.739
if you're doing things 
like featured snippet optimization 

159
00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:34.019
or other things.

160
00:09:34.019 --> 00:09:36.021
But for accessibility, 

161
00:09:36.021 --> 00:09:39.676
screen readers will parse 
unordered lists 

162
00:09:39.676 --> 00:09:41.329
of links for menus.

163
00:09:41.329 --> 00:09:46.025
It's really helpful 
to think about organizing, 

164
00:09:46.025 --> 00:09:52.739
your navigation, especially sub-navigation 
or tertiary navigations, 

165
00:09:52.739 --> 00:09:55.005
into unordered list, 

166
00:09:55.005 --> 00:09:58.350
for both SEO and accessibility.

167
00:09:58.350 --> 00:10:01.029
Anchor Text: So this is our first item 

168
00:10:01.029 --> 00:10:03.434
that has a little bit of conflict. 

169
00:10:03.434 --> 00:10:06.441
We'll start with the SEO part of it. 

170
00:10:06.441 --> 00:10:09.089
Search engines use anchor text 

171
00:10:09.089 --> 00:10:13.570
to associate keywords 
within target pages 

172
00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:16.000
that those links are linked to.

173
00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:19.377
When we talk about anchor text, 
we're talking about 

174
00:10:19.377 --> 00:10:22.000
the text found within a link

175
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.961
and for SEO, search engines 

176
00:10:24.961 --> 00:10:29.891
use that text to associate 
the terminology 

177
00:10:29.891 --> 00:10:32.500
that should be associated 
with the page 

178
00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:34.257
that the link is pointing to. 

179
00:10:34.257 --> 00:10:36.545
Then for accessibility, 

180
00:10:36.545 --> 00:10:39.501
screen readers will list links 

181
00:10:39.501 --> 00:10:41.710
independently of content.

182
00:10:41.710 --> 00:10:44.796
Therefore, anchor text 
should not rely 

183
00:10:44.796 --> 00:10:49.515
on the context of the content, 
it is found in. 

184
00:10:49.515 --> 00:10:51.328
In other words, 
your anchor text 

185
00:10:51.328 --> 00:10:57.430
should never be like, click here, 
or download this.

186
00:10:57.430 --> 00:10:59.652
It should always 
be descriptive 

187
00:10:59.652 --> 00:11:01.874
of the page that 
it's linking to

188
00:11:01.874 --> 00:11:03.680
so that when those links

189
00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:06.137
are pulled out of the content 

190
00:11:06.137 --> 00:11:10.069
and made into a 
independent navigation menu,

191
00:11:10.069 --> 00:11:14.389
it's easier to understand 
what those links go to. 

192
00:11:14.389 --> 00:11:15.772
Some conflicts. 

193
00:11:15.772 --> 00:11:18.571
SEOs have a tendency to stuff 

194
00:11:18.571 --> 00:11:22.304
a bunch of keywords 
within anchor text. 

195
00:11:22.304 --> 00:11:25.290
Like I said before, 
it's because

196
00:11:25.290 --> 00:11:27.715
that anchor text can influence 

197
00:11:27.715 --> 00:11:30.374
the terms that 
the search engines 

198
00:11:30.374 --> 00:11:32.924
will associate with 
that target page. 

199
00:11:34.924 --> 00:11:36.000
You want to 
make sure that 

200
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:39.104
as you are optimizing 
your anchor text, 

201
00:11:39.104 --> 00:11:43.523
that that anchor text 
is also useful for accessibility. 

202
00:11:43.523 --> 00:11:44.510
You don't want to jam up 

203
00:11:44.510 --> 00:11:47.689
a bunch of keywords 
in your anchor text 

204
00:11:47.689 --> 00:11:50.709
so that when 
those links are taken out

205
00:11:50.709 --> 00:11:52.411
of the content mega menu, 

206
00:11:52.411 --> 00:11:55.675
they still have
to make sense. 

207
00:11:55.675 --> 00:11:57.143
It's really important for SEOs 

208
00:11:57.143 --> 00:12:01.783
not to jam up a bunch of keywords
into the anchor text 

209
00:12:01.783 --> 00:12:06.225
and make for a bad navigation 
for screen readers. 

210
00:12:06.225 --> 00:12:10.246
Let's look at content optimization.

211
00:12:10.246 --> 00:12:16.562
Heading tags, these are 
like your H1, H2, H3 tags. 

212
00:12:16.562 --> 00:12:20.069
For SEO, they should 
structure the content 

213
00:12:20.069 --> 00:12:22.899
with main and sub-headings,

214
00:12:22.899 --> 00:12:25.916
use tags consecutively 

215
00:12:25.916 --> 00:12:28.000
and include the target terms. 

216
00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.005
Generally you want to use 

217
00:12:30.005 --> 00:12:33.285
one H1 tag per page 

218
00:12:33.285 --> 00:12:34.884
and then underneath that 

219
00:12:34.884 --> 00:12:41.139
use consecutive order: H2, H3, H4, down. 

220
00:12:41.139 --> 00:12:44.865
For accessibility, 
screen readers 

221
00:12:44.865 --> 00:12:47.063
use these heading tags 

222
00:12:47.063 --> 00:12:49.967
for content navigation. 

223
00:12:47.967 --> 00:12:51.741
Again, you wanna
use the same structure 

224
00:12:51.741 --> 00:12:53.875
they would use for SEO 

225
00:12:53.875 --> 00:12:59.121
and use a very descriptive content

226
00:12:59.121 --> 00:13:01.347
within the heading tags 

227
00:13:01.347 --> 00:13:04.162
that would describe the content 
for that section of the page.

228
00:13:04.162 --> 00:13:08.868
A good balance for SEO 
and accessibility, is that, 

229
00:13:08.868 --> 00:13:12.913
you can label 
these heading tags 

230
00:13:12.913 --> 00:13:17.706
with content that includes 
descriptive keywords 

231
00:13:17.706 --> 00:13:21.628
that also describe the content 

232
00:13:21.628 --> 00:13:25.550
that the headings represent.

233
00:13:25.550 --> 00:13:30.806
Title Tags: Title tags are 
a very important part of SEO

234
00:13:30.806 --> 00:13:33.581
and so title tag should include

235
00:13:33.581 --> 00:13:38.029
unique targeting keywords 
for rankings of

236
00:13:38.029 --> 00:13:41.100
increased clickthrough rates.

237
00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:43.536
For accessibility, title tags 

238
00:13:43.536 --> 00:13:47.108
should include 
unique terms for navigation. 

239
00:13:47.108 --> 00:13:49.852
A conflict that 
I see sometimes 

240
00:13:49.852 --> 00:13:52.339
is that SEOs 
sometimes include

241
00:13:52.339 --> 00:13:56.851
marketing language in the content 
in the title tags, 

242
00:13:56.851 --> 00:13:59.961
such as clickthrough 
calls to action, 

243
00:13:59.961 --> 00:14:02.499
to increase clickthrough rates.

244
00:14:02.499 --> 00:14:05.802
Basically the reason this happens is, 

245
00:14:05.802 --> 00:14:08.260
because the search snippet, 

246
00:14:08.260 --> 00:14:12.122
the what you see within 
the search results, 

247
00:14:12.122 --> 00:14:15.870
that title there is 
taken from a title tag 

248
00:14:15.870 --> 00:14:19.094
and so SEOs oftentimes 
like to write 

249
00:14:19.094 --> 00:14:22.220
kind of eye-popping 
marketing language 

250
00:14:22.220 --> 00:14:25.069
within the title tag 
to get users 

251
00:14:25.069 --> 00:14:31.058
to click on their search result, 
within the search rankings.

252
00:14:31.058 --> 00:14:35.086
That's fine, but a problem 
with that is that, 

253
00:14:35.086 --> 00:14:39.327
that can get in the way of providing 

254
00:14:39.327 --> 00:14:41.604
a useful navigation item. 

255
00:14:41.604 --> 00:14:44.234
If you think about title tags 

256
00:14:44.234 --> 00:14:47.741
as a way to navigate 
through the pages, 

257
00:14:47.741 --> 00:14:51.255
either through using tabs 
on your browser, 

258
00:14:51.255 --> 00:14:56.606
or navigation within a list 
of bookmarks,

259
00:14:56.606 --> 00:15:00.015
you should keep your title tags 

260
00:15:00.015 --> 00:15:01.743
as easy to understand
as possible. 

261
00:15:01.743 --> 00:15:04.583
If you can find 
a good balance between 

262
00:15:04.583 --> 00:15:06.950
having a good call to action, 

263
00:15:06.950 --> 00:15:10.353
but also making it concise 

264
00:15:10.353 --> 00:15:16.876
and easy to understand, 
that's the best method. 

265
00:15:16.876 --> 00:15:19.930
Keywords and Language:

266
00:15:19.930 --> 00:15:23.450
You want to use keywords for SEO 

267
00:15:23.450 --> 00:15:25.370
in a natural way. 

268
00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:31.939
Historically SEOs have been 
notorious about

269
00:15:31.939 --> 00:15:35.129
pumping a bunch of keywords 
in the content

270
00:15:35.129 --> 00:15:39.708
and trying to force their content 
into those results. 

271
00:15:39.708 --> 00:15:44.288
That's no longer as popular
anymore as it used to be, 

272
00:15:44.288 --> 00:15:47.938
which is a good thing, 
because for accessibility, 

273
00:15:47.938 --> 00:15:51.660
content should adhere 
to good readability standards

274
00:15:51.660 --> 00:15:53.891
and should be easily understood. 

275
00:15:53.891 --> 00:15:57.137
These two things really 
go together in my mind, 

276
00:15:57.137 --> 00:15:59.170
because the search engines 

277
00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:01.957
are starting to employ 
more and more 

278
00:16:01.957 --> 00:16:03.990
natural language processing

279
00:16:03.990 --> 00:16:07.507
which attempts to 
understand the content 

280
00:16:07.507 --> 00:16:10.681
the way a human being 
would read it. 

281
00:16:10.681 --> 00:16:17.236
Therefore, using a bunch of 
targeted keywords,

282
00:16:17.236 --> 00:16:19.000
and writing your content 

283
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:21.204
in a way that doesn't sound natural,

284
00:16:21.204 --> 00:16:23.129
may be not so smart 

285
00:16:23.129 --> 00:16:26.209
for either SEO or accessibility.

286
00:16:26.209 --> 00:16:29.356
It's always good 
to use natural language

287
00:16:29.356 --> 00:16:32.465
and to use content 
that makes sense 

288
00:16:32.465 --> 00:16:38.992
for all users, search engines, 
and human beings. 

289
00:16:38.992 --> 00:16:43.021
Hidden Content: I saw this mentioned 

290
00:16:43.021 --> 00:16:46.731
earlier today in someone's talk 

291
00:16:46.731 --> 00:16:49.475
and for SEO, hidden content 

292
00:16:49.475 --> 00:16:52.871
is not detected 
by search engines. 

293
00:16:52.871 --> 00:16:55.346
In some cases it can be 

294
00:16:55.346 --> 00:16:59.470
a violation of their 
quality guidelines.

295
00:16:59.470 --> 00:17:04.498
In accessibility, 
you can hide content 

296
00:17:04.498 --> 00:17:06.948
from visual users, 

297
00:17:06.948 --> 00:17:11.574
but then make it accessible 
to screen readers 

298
00:17:11.574 --> 00:17:13.446
and there's different reasons 

299
00:17:13.446 --> 00:17:15.381
why you might want to do this. 

300
00:17:15.381 --> 00:17:17.422
For example, you might have 

301
00:17:17.422 --> 00:17:20.827
a completely separate navigation 

302
00:17:20.827 --> 00:17:21.649
just for screen readers, 

303
00:17:21.649 --> 00:17:28.936
but you don't want that navigation 
to be visible to visual users. 

304
00:17:28.936 --> 00:17:30.812
That's understandable, 

305
00:17:30.812 --> 00:17:33.422
but accessibility professionals

306
00:17:33.422 --> 00:17:35.379
should not hide content 

307
00:17:35.379 --> 00:17:38.392
that is critical for SEO. 

308
00:17:38.392 --> 00:17:40.651
This is just common sense
in a way, 

309
00:17:40.651 --> 00:17:43.820
because if we 
follow the principles

310
00:17:43.820 --> 00:17:46.509
of universal design, 

311
00:17:46.509 --> 00:17:50.748
